2026-03-09 14:20:27,648 - ThreadPoolExecutor-0_0 - INFO - {'status': 'OK', 'InterviewDetails': {'Id': 16225, 'TestUserId': 3838065, 'EventId': 17924, 'ApplicantId': 1407881, 'Experience': 3, 'FavoriteProject': 'E-commerce platform redesign', 'IsEnded': True, 'InterviewDate': '2025-12-02T16:55:38', 'DetailedFeedback': [{'QuestionCategory': 'Introduction', 'QuestionAnswers': [{'Question': 'Hi, Good day! welcome to interview, brief about yourself', 'QuestionUrl': 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/ams-in-self-expiring-files/30-720h/159/735d928a-4c74-4e28-9a7c-b2715e70ffda_tta.ogg?AWSAccessKeyId=AKIAIPKT65FIXSXQGDOQ&Signature=U0%2B3F3a%2FnzDHgzv8Y9Nn4qYN84s%3D&Expires=1773046527', 'Answer': "Hi, I'manobis Nirmal and currently I'm working at XYZ. I have experience with UI designing, especially with Figma and Adobe Illustrator. I have some experience in photo editing and video editing as well. For photo and video, I use Premiere Pro and Photoshop.", 'Feedback': 'The candidate provided a concise introduction, mentioning their current employment and relevant skills in UI design and multimedia editing. The response is relevant and covers key aspects of their professional background.', 'AnswerUrl': ['https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/test-all-hirepro-files/OpenAiInterviewTextToAudio/61d76407-ee3a-4c79-9c85-a3d106ff947fblob.webm?AWSAccessKeyId=AKIAIPKT65FIXSXQGDOQ&Signature=mF3O%2BoiUcvmKmMZR66EeThk5Gic%3D&Expires=1773046527'], 'Score': '8.0', 'QuestionCategory': 'Introduction', 'ExpectedAnswer': "An ideal answer would include a brief introduction of the candidate's name, current role, and a summary of their professional experience and skills, particularly highlighting any relevant skills or projects that align with the job they are interviewing for.", 'ScoreExplanation': "The candidate's answer is relevant and provides a clear overview of their professional background, including their current job and skills in UI design and multimedia editing. The response is concise and covers multiple key aspects, which aligns well with the expected answer for an introduction question. The score reflects the completeness and relevance of the response.", 'Communication_feedback': None, 'Authenticity_feedback': None, 'SkillConcept': None, 'QuestionType': 5, 'QuestionTypeText': 'Verbal'}]}, {'QuestionCategory': 'Testing', 'QuestionAnswers': [{'Question': "That's an interesting background, Norval! Now, can you tell me what role ChromeDriver plays in automation testing?", 'QuestionUrl': None, 'Answer': 'Yes sure, so ChromeDriver is basically a software which helps you to execute the task that it will retain on your code and help to execute the task by connecting your code with a browser, real time browser and in this case, especially the Chrome browser. So whenever you run a code, you need the Chrome browser to execute the same task, ChromeDriver to execute the same task in a browser.', 'Feedback': "The answer provides a basic understanding of ChromeDriver's role in automation testing, mentioning its function in connecting code with the Chrome browser. However, it lacks depth and specific details about how it interacts with Selenium WebDriver and its role in executing automated tests.", 'AnswerUrl': ['https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/test-all-hirepro-files/OpenAiInterviewTextToAudio/9a0a9e45-9156-472b-bc28-a33314fa94deblob.webm?AWSAccessKeyId=AKIAIPKT65FIXSXQGDOQ&Signature=SXtgwm9G7zLDfhQcqzBHFkrb7ZM%3D&Expires=1773046527'], 'Score': '5.0', 'QuestionCategory': 'Testing', 'ExpectedAnswer': 'ChromeDriver is a standalone server that implements the WebDriver protocol for Chrome. It acts as a bridge between Selenium WebDriver and the Chrome browser, allowing automated tests to be executed in the Chrome browser. ChromeDriver translates the WebDriver commands into Chrome-specific commands, enabling the automation of browser actions such as clicking, typing, and navigating.', 'ScoreExplanation': "The question asks for the role of ChromeDriver in automation testing, expecting an explanation of its function and interaction with Selenium WebDriver. The candidate's answer correctly identifies ChromeDriver as a tool for executing tasks in the Chrome browser but lacks detail on its specific role in automation testing, such as its interaction with Selenium WebDriver. The answer is correct but minimal, providing a basic definition without elaboration or examples, which limits the score to 5.", 'Communication_feedback': None, 'Authenticity_feedback': None, 'SkillConcept': None, 'QuestionType': 5, 'QuestionTypeText': 'Verbal'}]}, {'QuestionCategory': 'Project', 'QuestionAnswers': [{'Question': "That's an interesting approach! Now, how would you approach testing the user interface of a redesigned e-commerce platform to ensure it meets usability and accessibility standards?", 'QuestionUrl': None, 'Answer': 'Okay, so to check the usability and accessibility standards, there are a couple of ways that you can proceed when you are building a component or building a software specifically. So first, you first generally create the software, you do the basic testing, once the basic testing is done and the bugs are gone, then you create a beta version of it, and then you have two options, you can make it available for the public and gather, make the beta version available for the public and gather info from there, I mean, and the feedbacks will help you to get the user accessibility and stabilize the software. And the second thing you can do is, with your testing team only, you do a UI UX testing and just to make sure that the things are working or not, from there also you can gather feedback and make the changes as per needed.', 'Feedback': 'The answer outlines a general approach to testing but lacks specific steps or techniques for ensuring usability and accessibility standards. It mentions basic testing, beta testing, and gathering feedback, but does not detail specific usability or accessibility testing methods.', 'AnswerUrl': ['https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/test-all-hirepro-files/OpenAiInterviewTextToAudio/31b81d59-9065-485a-b7e2-cdaf72318957blob.webm?AWSAccessKeyId=AKIAIPKT65FIXSXQGDOQ&Signature=Nf98L6dgr0J87eFRVV7q3Ls6q8E%3D&Expires=1773046527', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/test-all-hirepro-files/OpenAiInterviewTextToAudio/747c9fb5-32a3-4f18-a9b5-fa2a5fd96deeblob.webm?AWSAccessKeyId=AKIAIPKT65FIXSXQGDOQ&Signature=t%2F32Iy%2BMWVuIAwjBjxkusjf%2B6Ig%3D&Expires=1773046527'], 'Score': '5.0', 'QuestionCategory': 'Project', 'ExpectedAnswer': 'To test the user interface of a redesigned e-commerce platform for usability and accessibility, start with usability testing by conducting user interviews and usability tests with real users to gather feedback on the interface. Use tools like screen readers to test accessibility and ensure compliance with standards like WCAG. Perform heuristic evaluations and cognitive walkthroughs to identify usability issues. Conduct A/B testing to compare different design versions. Finally, gather feedback from a diverse group of users, including those with disabilities, to ensure the platform is accessible to all.', 'ScoreExplanation': "The question asks for an approach to testing the UI for usability and accessibility, expecting a detailed explanation of steps or techniques. The candidate's answer provides a general process but lacks specific methods for usability and accessibility testing, such as using screen readers or conducting heuristic evaluations. The answer mentions beta testing and feedback gathering, which are relevant but not sufficient for a comprehensive approach. Therefore, the score is capped at 5 due to the lack of specific techniques and detailed steps.", 'Communication_feedback': None, 'Authenticity_feedback': None, 'SkillConcept': None, 'QuestionType': 5, 'QuestionTypeText': 'Verbal'}]}, {'QuestionCategory': 'manual testing', 'QuestionAnswers': [{'Question': "Thanks for sharing! Let's move on to how you decide which test cases to execute manually.", 'QuestionUrl': 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/test-all-hirepro-files/OpenAiInterviewTextToAudio/68daab5e-baf6-4116-84b8-b856cba2883d_tta.ogg?AWSAccessKeyId=AKIAIPKT65FIXSXQGDOQ&Signature=rSmia3pCYdBU6NO7lMckUm9pyRI%3D&Expires=1773046527', 'Answer': 'So there are various ways where we can get to determine that which of the test cases that we have to execute manually. In the initial state, basically all of the test cases that we check manually for the first cycle. Then we determine that which of the test cases can be automated, which are very much repetitive and can be handled by automation. And where no human interaction is required in those type of test cases, we automate. And rest of the test cases that are available where human intervention is very much needed and not possible to repeat the task using bot or something. Those cases we generally handle by manual testing.', 'Feedback': 'The candidate provides a general approach to deciding which test cases to execute manually, mentioning initial manual execution and automation of repetitive tasks. However, the answer lacks specific criteria or examples for decision-making.', 'AnswerUrl': ['https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/test-all-hirepro-files/OpenAiInterviewTextToAudio/12a42eb4-4ea8-48f0-9b53-88ba58d9694dblob.webm?AWSAccessKeyId=AKIAIPKT65FIXSXQGDOQ&Signature=uOcH%2Bp868We6Sfj68SNzloUpDOY%3D&Expires=1773046527'], 'Score': '6.0', 'QuestionCategory': 'manual testing', 'ExpectedAnswer': 'To decide which test cases to execute manually, consider the following criteria: 1) Complexity: Test cases that require human judgment or are too complex for automation should be executed manually. 2) Frequency: Test cases that are not frequently executed may not justify the cost of automation. 3) Changes: Test cases that frequently change may be better suited for manual execution. 4) Exploratory Testing: Scenarios that require exploratory testing or ad-hoc testing are best handled manua