acoustic_result': 'spontaneous'}, 'SkillConcept': None, 'QuestionType': 5, 'QuestionTypeText': 'Verbal'}]}, {'QuestionCategory': 'Project', 'QuestionAnswers': [{'Question': "That's an interesting approach! Now, how would you approach testing the user interface of a redesigned e-commerce platform to ensure it meets usability and accessibility standards?", 'QuestionUrl': None, 'Answer': 'Okay, so to check the usability and accessibility standards, there are a couple of ways that you can proceed when you are building a component or building a software specifically. So first, you first generally create the software, you do the basic testing, once the basic testing is done and the bugs are gone, then you create a beta version of it, and then you have two options, you can make it available for the public and gather, make the beta version available for the public and gather info from there, I mean, and the feedbacks will help you to get the user accessibility and stabilize the software. And the second thing you can do is, with your testing team only, you do a UI UX testing and just to make sure that the things are working or not, from there also you can gather feedback and make the changes as per needed.', 'Feedback': 'The answer outlines a general approach to testing but lacks specific steps or techniques for ensuring usability and accessibility standards. It mentions basic testing, beta testing, and gathering feedback but does not detail specific usability or accessibility testing methods.', 'AnswerUrl': ['https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/test-all-hirepro-files/OpenAiInterviewTextToAudio/31b81d59-9065-485a-b7e2-cdaf72318957blob.webm?AWSAccessKeyId=AKIAIPKT65FIXSXQGDOQ&Signature=Ks8d3Tawd%2FoT4CQvKz%2BjGQjO8X0%3D&Expires=1773051037', 'https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/test-all-hirepro-files/OpenAiInterviewTextToAudio/747c9fb5-32a3-4f18-a9b5-fa2a5fd96deeblob.webm?AWSAccessKeyId=AKIAIPKT65FIXSXQGDOQ&Signature=rPwO0O0AjiTbfqt%2BAMdk4j47iP4%3D&Expires=1773051037'